caption: A lovely green space that has plenty of seating to enjoy the tranquillity the surrounds of the park was busy with the area, vide greinier, (car booty/flea market), it was a fun time to visit

Nice small neighbourhood park. Equipped with a basketball court, a ping pong table and a good selection of slides and swings. It is pretty well kept, and mostly frequented by the more well-off ''bobo'' inhabitants of the neighbourhood, although I am told there used to be the odd used syringe in the bushes, so keep an eye out if you're  with small kids. I think it's very safe and clean during the day, perhaps not so much at night, but you're not supposed to go there at night anyway. It's a nice quiet oasis in an otherwise noisy and rather hectic area.
Nice and relaxing. Great place to chill.
We like this place! It’a nice and relaxing for a little picnic while your kids play! It’s just missing some more games for big kids!
A great place for a rest or a sun filled lunch surrounded by lush plantings.
nice place to rest few minutes good park for kids
A nice place to just enjoy a rest before walking more or to be immersed in some day-to-day life of parisian kids.
Beautiful peaceful park with lots of shade to enjoy your lunch or meet up with friends.
Beautiful anytime of year!

An adorable little park with beautiful scenery. There's a big play area for kids up to age ten. There are some ancient trees overlooking the many benches. The people owning the stores surrounding the park are very friendly.  There are a lot of homeless people sleeping on the benches, though.

Bad luck for me so I'll let it reflect the review: 2min after entering the park a homeless beggar came, wasted out of his mind. That's fine and expected in big city but in the middle of the kids park it's not so nice. Also more homeless/drunkards were right outside the park
Lively, vibrant square with playgrounds, plenty of benches and public toilet.
Quiet park with many benches, idyllic location for a peaceful lunch.
It was so good and it had  fountains !
Popular Island of Green in the city to spend some time reflecting.
To rest on a bench. Clean small park. There is a kids playground and a basketball field. I didn't find a tap water fountain there...

Good place to let the kids run around for a second in the middle of Paris.  Playground for the little ones.
Lots of benches to sit on in the shade and multiple age-appropriate climbing structures for kids.
